Pests and disease, which destroyed 1.1mln tonnes of wheat in China in 1986, are threatening crops on11.64 mln hectares this year, the China Daily said.    About 14.54 mln hectares of wheat were affected in 1986.    The paper said abnormal weather conditions had encouragedthe spread of wheat midges in 2.47 mln hectares in Shanxi,Henan, Sichuan, Anhui, Hebei and Jiangsu.    In Henan, Shandong and Hebei wheat aphids are affecting4.67 mln hectares, wheat red mite 2.8 mln hectares and wheatpowdery mildew 1.7 mln hectares. REUTER&#3;